# Site profile for Purdue Gilbreth (Spack/Lmod + system Anaconda). Copy to site.env:
#   cp deconvolution/setup/site.env.gilbreth.example deconvolution/setup/site.env
# and adjust the module versions/conda prefix for your own cluster. install_r_env.sh
# sources this if present. On a laptop/server with R installed, you need NO site.env.
#
# Modules to load before installing/running. Beyond R itself these supply the build-time
# system headers the bare conda env lacks (verified necessary on Gilbreth):
#   libpng -> png.h (Seurat's png dep) | zlib -> zlib.h | cmake -> nloptr
#   (libxml2/curl/libtiff arrive with the r module; openssl/ICU headers come from conda's
#    include dir, which we deliberately keep on CPATH -- see STRIP_CONDA below.)
R_MODULES="r/4.4.1 libpng/1.6.37 zlib/1.3.1 cmake/3.30.2"

# Conda prefix to strip from PATH/PKG_CONFIG_PATH (NOT CPATH). On Gilbreth the system
# Anaconda's libstdc++ otherwise shadows the module gcc and breaks scran/igraph dlopen.
STRIP_CONDA="/apps/external/conda/2025.09"

# Where to install (project-local lib keeps the shared module R clean). Optional.
# R_LIBS_USER="${PROJECT_ROOT}/R_libs"
